### Message APIs - REST Client Testing
### Use with VS Code REST Client extension or Thunder Client

@baseUrl = http://localhost:5000/api
@token = YOUR_JWT_TOKEN_HERE
@conversationId = YOUR_CONVERSATION_ID_HERE
@messageId = YOUR_MESSAGE_ID_HERE

### ═══════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════
### Setup: Create users, conversation, and get tokens
### ═══════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════

### Register User 1
POST {{baseUrl}}/auth/register
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "name": "Alice Johnson",
  "email": "alice@example.com",
  "password": "AlicePass123",
  "confirmPassword": "AlicePass123"
}

### Login User 1 (save token as @token)
POST {{baseUrl}}/auth/login
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "email": "alice@example.com",
  "password": "AlicePass123"
}

### Register User 2
POST {{baseUrl}}/auth/register
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "name": "Bob Smith",
  "email": "bob@example.com",
  "password": "BobPass123",
  "confirmPassword": "BobPass123"
}

### Create conversation (save ID as @conversationId)
POST {{baseUrl}}/conversations
Authorization: Bearer {{token}}
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "otherUserId": "BOB_USER_ID_HERE"
}

### ═══════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════
### 1. SEND MESSAGES
### ═══════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════

### Send first message
POST {{baseUrl}}/messages
Authorization: Bearer {{token}}
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "conversationId": "{{conversationId}}",
  "text": "Hey Bob! How are you?"
}

### Send second message (save message ID as @messageId)
POST {{baseUrl}}/messages
Authorization: Bearer {{token}}
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "conversationId": "{{conversationId}}",
  "text": "This is a test message"
}

### Send third message
POST {{baseUrl}}/messages
Authorization: Bearer {{token}}
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "conversationId": "{{conversationId}}",
  "text": "Let me know when you're available!"
}

### Send message with special characters
POST {{baseUrl}}/messages
Authorization: Bearer {{token}}
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "conversationId": "{{conversationId}}",
  "text": "Hello! 👋 Check this out: https://example.com 🎉"
}

### Send message with extra whitespace (tests trimming)
POST {{baseUrl}}/messages
Authorization: Bearer {{token}}
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "conversationId": "{{conversationId}}",
  "text": "   Message with extra spaces   "
}

### ═══════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════
### 2. GET MESSAGES (PAGINATED)
### ═══════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════

### Get all messages (default pagination)
GET {{baseUrl}}/messages/{{conversationId}}
Authorization: Bearer {{token}}

### Get messages with custom limit
GET {{baseUrl}}/messages/{{conversationId}}?limit=2
Authorization: Bearer {{token}}

### Get messages page 1 with limit 2
GET {{baseUrl}}/messages/{{conversationId}}?page=1&limit=2
Authorization: Bearer {{token}}

### Get messages page 2
GET {{baseUrl}}/messages/{{conversationId}}?page=2&limit=2
Authorization: Bearer {{token}}

### Get messages with large limit
GET {{baseUrl}}/messages/{{conversationId}}?limit=50
Authorization: Bearer {{token}}

### ═══════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════
### 3. MARK MESSAGES AS READ
### ═══════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════

### Mark message as read (replace {{messageId}} with real ID from send response)
PATCH {{baseUrl}}/messages/{{messageId}}/read
Authorization: Bearer {{token}}

### Mark another message as read
PATCH {{baseUrl}}/messages/MESSAGE_ID_2_HERE/read
Authorization: Bearer {{token}}

### Mark message as read again (idempotent test)
PATCH {{baseUrl}}/messages/{{messageId}}/read
Authorization: Bearer {{token}}

### ═══════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════
### ERROR CASES & VALIDATION
### ═══════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════

### Send message without text
POST {{baseUrl}}/messages
Authorization: Bearer {{token}}
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "conversationId": "{{conversationId}}"
}

### Send message without conversation ID
POST {{baseUrl}}/messages
Authorization: Bearer {{token}}
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "text": "Hello world"
}

### Send empty message
POST {{baseUrl}}/messages
Authorization: Bearer {{token}}
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "conversationId": "{{conversationId}}",
  "text": ""
}

### Send message with text too long (>5000 chars)
POST {{baseUrl}}/messages
Authorization: Bearer {{token}}
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "conversationId": "{{conversationId}}",
  "text": ""
}

### Send message with invalid conversation ID format
POST {{baseUrl}}/messages
Authorization: Bearer {{token}}
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "conversationId": "invalid-id",
  "text": "Hello"
}

### Send message with non-existent conversation
POST {{baseUrl}}/messages
Authorization: Bearer {{token}}
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "conversationId": "000000000000000000000000",
  "text": "Hello"
}

### Get messages with invalid conversation ID
GET {{baseUrl}}/messages/invalid-id
Authorization: Bearer {{token}}

### Get messages from non-existent conversation
GET {{baseUrl}}/messages/000000000000000000000000
Authorization: Bearer {{token}}

### Get messages as non-participant (unauthorized)
### First create conversation between Alice and Bob, then try accessing with Charlie
GET {{baseUrl}}/messages/ALICE_BOB_CONV_ID
Authorization: Bearer CHARLIE_TOKEN_HERE

### Mark invalid message ID as read
PATCH {{baseUrl}}/messages/invalid-id/read
Authorization: Bearer {{token}}

### Mark non-existent message as read
PATCH {{baseUrl}}/messages/000000000000000000000000/read
Authorization: Bearer {{token}}

### ═══════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════
### PAGINATION TESTING
### ═══════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════

### Get messages with invalid page (0)
GET {{baseUrl}}/messages/{{conversationId}}?page=0
Authorization: Bearer {{token}}

### Get messages with invalid limit (0)
GET {{baseUrl}}/messages/{{conversationId}}?limit=0
Authorization: Bearer {{token}}

### Get messages with limit exceeding max (>100)
GET {{baseUrl}}/messages/{{conversationId}}?limit=200
Authorization: Bearer {{token}}

### Get messages with non-numeric pagination
GET {{baseUrl}}/messages/{{conversationId}}?page=abc&limit=xyz
Authorization: Bearer {{token}}

### ═══════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════
### AUTHENTICATION ERRORS
### ═══════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════

### No authorization header
GET {{baseUrl}}/messages/{{conversationId}}

### Invalid token
GET {{baseUrl}}/messages/{{conversationId}}
Authorization: Bearer invalid-token-here

### Send message without token
POST {{baseUrl}}/messages
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "conversationId": "{{conversationId}}",
  "text": "Hello"
}

### ═══════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════
### MESSAGING WORKFLOW
### ═══════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════

### 1. Create conversation with another user
POST {{baseUrl}}/conversations
Authorization: Bearer {{token}}
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "otherUserId": "OTHER_USER_ID"
}

### 2. Send initial message
POST {{baseUrl}}/messages
Authorization: Bearer {{token}}
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "conversationId": "CONV_ID",
  "text": "Hey, want to chat?"
}

### 3. Load message history (page 1)
GET {{baseUrl}}/messages/CONV_ID?page=1&limit=20
Authorization: Bearer {{token}}

### 4. If hasMore=true, load next page
GET {{baseUrl}}/messages/CONV_ID?page=2&limit=20
Authorization: Bearer {{token}}

### 5. Mark message as read
PATCH {{baseUrl}}/messages/MSG_ID/read
Authorization: Bearer {{token}}

### ═══════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════
### NOTES FOR TESTING
### ═══════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════
###
### 1. Replace {{token}} with actual JWT token from login response
###    - Run login request
###    - Copy data.token
###    - Set @token = <copied_token>
###
### 2. Replace {{conversationId}} with actual conversation ID
###    - Run conversation creation or GET /api/conversations
###    - Copy conversation._id
###    - Set @conversationId = <copied_id>
###
### 3. Replace {{messageId}} with actual message ID from send response
###    - Run send message request
###    - Copy _id from response
###    - Set @messageId = <copied_id>
###
### 4. Message Order:
###    - GET returns messages OLDEST TO NEWEST (natural chat order)
###    - Database stores with ascending timestamps
###    - Frontend appends new, loads old at top
###
### 5. Pagination:
###    - page=1, limit=20 → messages 1-20
###    - Check hasMore: true to continue
###    - Don't miss pages or you'll have gaps
###
### 6. Read Receipts:
###    - readBy array tracks who read the message
###    - Each entry has userId and readAt timestamp
###    - Frontend can show "Read by" indicator
###
### 7. Response Schema:
###    {
###      "success": true/false,
###      "data": { /* message/pagination data */ },
###      "message": "Success or error message",
###      "statusCode": 200/201/400/403/404
###    }
###
### 8. Test Flow:
###    a. Create two users and login (get tokens)
###    b. Use User 1 token to create conversation with User 2
###    c. User 1 sends messages
###    d. User 1 retrieves messages (verify order and content)
###    e. User 1 marks messages as read
###    f. Test unauthorized access (use User 2 or non-participant)
###    g. Test validation (empty text, invalid IDs, etc.)
###
